## DuplicateRenderPartialArguments

**Severity:** warning | **Type:** LiquidHtml | **Aliases:** `DuplicateRenderPartialParams`

This check ensures that no duplicate argument names are provided when rendering a partial using the `{% raw %}{% render %}{% endraw %}` tag. Passing the same argument twice is always a mistake — only one value will be used at runtime.

## Examples

### &#x2717; Incorrect Code Example (Avoid using this):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% render 'card', title: "Hello", title: "World" %}
{% endraw %}
```

The `title` argument is passed twice.

### &#x2713; Correct Code Example (Use this instead):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% render 'card', title: "Hello" %}
{% endraw %}
```

## Configuration

The default configuration for this check:

```yaml
DuplicateRenderPartialArguments:
  enabled: true
  severity: warning
```

## Disabling This Check

Disabling this check is not recommended. Duplicate arguments are always a mistake.

